description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Tennessee Jed, CC Rider, Friend Of The Devil, Mama Tried-> Mexicali Blues, Bird Song, Let It Grow-> Deal

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, Terrapin Station-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Iko Iko-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Good Lovin', E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Good but not great Honestly, after the two huge New Haven shows this was a step down. Well played enough but short and no jams to speak of. The band went from 55-60 minute pre-drums segments in NH to less than 35 minutes here. The ending first set trio was the highlight. 1981 was an excellent year but this wasn't one of the better efforts.

Also, the name of the New Orleans number that came out of space is Iko Iko. Only some Deadheads use that other, incorrect spelling, you'll never see it in the NOLA music world.
